<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 12 at 3:45PM EDT  by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern Union
County through 430 PM EDT...
At 345 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles north of Monroe, or near Unionville, moving northeast at 20
mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Monroe, Unionville, Fairview, Hemby Bridge, Indian Trail and New
Salem.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
